# Supabase Edge Functions

- Edge Functions are server-side TypeScript functions deployed globally on the Supabase Edge network.
- Use for custom backend logic, webhooks, API endpoints, and more.
- Deploy with `supabase functions deploy <name>`.
- Trigger via HTTP requests: `https://<project-ref>.functions.supabase.co/<function-name>`
- Environment variables can be set via the Supabase dashboard or CLI.
- Functions run in a secure, isolated environment with low cold start times.
- Use the Supabase CLI to create, test, and deploy functions.
- Docs: https://supabase.com/docs/guides/functions
